
Python PJSIP bindings
---------------------

- Add the MSRP transport class [RK]
- Document how other transports can be defined and  implemented (use MSRP as example) [RK]
- Handle PJSIP and Pyrex/Cython compilation in setup.py [RK]
- Properly decrease reference counts of pjsip_tx_data structs [RK]
- Fix remainig TODOs for PUBLISH/REGISTER [RK]
- Cleanup Registration, Publication and Subscription to behave more like Invitation [RK]
- Registration requestion URI should be settable by application [RK]
- High level Invitation class that handles SDP as well [RK]
- Add feature to send OPTIONS method and parse the replies [RK]
- Add ability for application to request handling of arbitrary methods such as [RK]
  OPTIONS, REGISTER and REFER, SUBSCRIBE (but not INVITE or NOTIFY...) and have it reply [RK]
- Handle sending and receiving of multipart bodies for Invitation  [RK]
- Handle UPDATE for re-INVITE [RK]
- Means to query RTP statistics [RK]
- Add option to use the STUN response for Contact header (default false) [RK]
- Make local_ip option settable at runtime [RK]
- Remove any DNS or lookups from pjsip (lookup is always done outside PJSIP) [RK]
- Survive IP address changes [RK]
- IPv6 support [RK]


